briefdescription.para: get size of hint rectangle for a particular dock location
wxAuiToolBar is a dockable toolbar, part of the wxAUI class framework.

detaileddescription.para: The appearance of this class is configurable and can be changed by calling wxAuiToolBar::SetArtProvider(). By default, native art provider is used if available (currently only in wxMSW) and wxAuiGenericToolBarArt otherwise.
This class supports the following styles:

listitem.para: wxAUI_TB_TEXT: Display the label strings on the toolbar buttons.
wxAUI_TB_NO_TOOLTIPS: Do not show tooltips for the toolbar items.
wxAUI_TB_NO_AUTORESIZE: Do not automatically resize the toolbar when new tools are added.
wxAUI_TB_GRIPPER: Show the toolbar's gripper control. If the toolbar is added to an AUI pane that contains a gripper, this style will be automatically set.
wxAUI_TB_OVERFLOW: Show an overflow menu containing toolbar items that can't fit on the toolbar if it is too small.

wxAUI_TB_VERTICAL: Using this style forces the toolbar to be vertical and be only dockable to the left or right sides of the window whereas by default it can be horizontal or vertical and be docked anywhere.
wxAUI_TB_HORIZONTAL: Analogous to wxAUI_TB_VERTICAL, but forces the toolbar to be horizontal.
wxAUI_TB_PLAIN_BACKGROUND: Draw a plain background (based on parent) instead of the default gradient background.
wxAUI_TB_DEFAULT_STYLE: The default is to have no styles.
